<li>Any promotional tickets offered by Vue or our partners, unless specified otherwise.</li>
</ol>
</li>
<li>No items other than tickets are cheaper online. This includes 3D glasses, which can purchased for the same price at the cinema and online.</li>
<li>For 3D films, you may purchase 3D glasses online or at the cinema. If you purchase them online, you will need to collect them at your chosen cinema along with your tickets.</li>
<li>Vue reserves the right to change prices at any time and without notice.</li>
<li>At the cinemas listed in paragraph 1 a booking fee is included in the online ticket price. The total amount payable will be displayed as the headline ticket price inclusive of the booking fee. By sending a request to book tickets, you agree to pay the booking fee incorporated in the headline ticket price. The total price paid for full priced standard tickets at these cinemas (excluding the tickets detailed in paragraph 3) is cheaper online inclusive of the booking fee paid.</li>
<li>Please note that no booking fee is payable for any tickets purchased in person at any of our cinemas, including at automated ticket machines on the premises. The price paid in the cinema (at the cinemas listed in paragraph 1) for full priced standard tickets (excluding the tickets detailed in paragraph 3) will be more expensive than the price paid online.</li>
<li>The total price paid for tickets purchased online for film screenings at the cinemas listed at paragraph 1 will be cheaper than the identical ticket purchased through the Booking Line.
<ol class="list">
<li>For all tickets purchased through the Booking Line, a booking fee for booking your ticket(s) remotely is payable in addition to the ticket price. This will be clearly notified to you during the booking process. The total amount payable will be inclusive of the booking fee. By sending a request to book tickets, you agree to pay the booking fee in addition to the ticket price.</li>
</ol>
</li>
